('LdAssetManagerImpl.java', 'org.semantictools.jsonld.impl.LdAssetManagerImpl', 'readAsset', '<[^:]*:schema', ' rdfs:comment "An OrderedValue represents a single letter grade within a ValueList. Each OrderedValue defines a letter grade that can be used as a score on an assignment, and it associates that letter grade with a range of numeric values. For example, the letter grade B might be associated with numeric scores in the range 80 to 90. The numeric range allows a learning application to submit a numeric score which is then mapped to a letter grade for display in the grade book. Ordinarily, the minimum value is included in the range, but the maximum value belongs to the next OrderedValue. For example, a score of exactly 90 would map to an A instead of a B. The last OrderedValue within a ValueList requires special treatment because it includes any value greater than or equal to the minimum value in the range. In this case, the maximum value represents the normal maximum without extra credit. Similarly, the first OrderedValue within a ValueList requires special treatment. It includes any numeric score that is strictly less than the maximum value in the associated ValueRange." .')

('LdAssetManagerImpl.java', 'org.semantictools.jsonld.impl.LdAssetManagerImpl', 'readAsset', '<[^:]*:schema', '  rdfs:comment "The default ResultValueSpec associated with this assignment.   The ResultValueSpec specifies whether scores on the assignment should be reported as floating point numbers or letter grades, and it provides constraints on those values.  As the name suggests, the defaultResultValueSpec is merely a default.  When an assignment is used in a learning context like a course section, it is associated with a GradebookItem that has its own resultValueSpec property.  Frequently, the resultValueSpec of the GradebookItem is  copy of the defaultResultValueSpec associated with the Assignment, but it may be different.  For example, extra credit points may be allowed or disallowed on a case-by-case basis.  " .')

If the GradebookItem is associated with an external Tool, this property indirectly identifies the Tool Proxy that defines the integration contract. This property points to the so-called ProductFamily to which the Tool belongs. The associated Tool Proxy is discovered by searching the context for a Tool Proxy Binding that matches a Tool in the specified family. This level of indirection allows for a Tool to be upgraded to a new version without breaking the grade book integration (or requiring all GradebookItems to be updated).

')

('LdAssetManagerImpl.java', 'org.semantictools.jsonld.impl.LdAssetManagerImpl', 'readAsset', '<[^:]*:schema', 'If the enclosing GradebookItem is associated with a ValueList, then the score may be submitted as a floating point number or a letter grade (string).  As a best practice, floating point numbers are prefered.  Based on the data in the ValueList, the receiving system will map numeric scores to letter grades for display purposes within the grade book and reports.  However, if it is not possible to submit a floating point score, the learning application may submit a string as the score.  In this case, the string must match one of the grades contained in the ValueList.""" .')
